#### 2.2.2 Actor: Customer
##### 2.2.2.1 Sign Up
A customer can sign up to create their profile with their name, email, password, and address. Emails must be unique.
##### 2.2.2.2 Log In
A customer shall be able to sign in using their registred email and password. After logging in, the customer shall be directed to the vehicle browsing page where they can begin their search.
##### 2.2.2.3 Browse Vehicles
A customer shall be able to view available Vehicles. They can do this from the home page or using a search function. They can also filter vehicles by make, model, color, and more. They will also be able to select a vehicle and view more details as each vehicle will be unique.
##### 2.2.2.4 Save Vehicles
A customer while searching and browsing shall be able to save any avaiable vehicle to their dahsboard where they can then access it at a later time, as long as the vehicle remains available.
##### 2.2.1.5 Purchase vehicle
Upon selecting a vehicle, a customer shall be able to contact the seller of the vehicle do discuss the terms of purchase. Once a deal is reached the seller will send a deal to the customer with their terms, if the customer accepts then the vehicle will then appear on their dashboard, and they will be able to complete the purchasing process.
##### 2.2.1.6 Review Seller
A customer may write a review for the seller, as each vehicle will be unique. They will be able to rate the seller based on thier experience.

